<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-03-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-03-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="631" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d631">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/367: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-26T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 26,
                                            1920—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>26. Your March 22, 8 p.m.</p>
                            <p>Arrangements have been made with Navy Department by which U.S.S. <hi rend="italic">Tacoma</hi> will be stationed for the present at
                                San José, Guatemala, and the U.S.S. <hi rend="italic">Niagara</hi>
                                at Puerto Barrios, Guatemalan Minister here states he is informed
                                all political prisoners have been released, also that President
                                Cabrera desires to accept Department’s plan as outlined. Department
                                desires further recommendations from you in regard to the situation.
                                Until further information is received from you, the Department is
                                unable to give further instructions.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>